  <Subject Subject_ID="300235119">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300235114</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>dependencies [300235114], political administrative bodies by degree of independence [300232417], political administrative bodies [300261086], administrative bodies [300000768], organizations (groups) [300025948], Organizations (hierarchy name) [300234770], Agents Facet [300264089]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Dependent communities, nations, or territories, which, by international treaty, are placed under the protection or domination of a foreign power or group of powers, typically entailing loss of control over such matters as defense and foreign relations.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Comunidades, naciones o territorios dependientes, en que por tratado internacional, están ubicadas bajo la protección o dominio de un poder extranjero o grupo de poderes, tipicamente conlleva una pérdida de control sobre materias tales como defensa y relaciones intenacionales.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Afhankelijke gemeenten, naties of territoria, die door internationale verdragen onder bescherming of beheer van een of meerdere buitenlandse mogendheden zijn geplaatst, waarvan het verlies van beheer over kwesties zoals defensie en buitenlandse relaties kenmerkend is.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指依照國際條約之規定，交託給一或多個外來強權保護或統治的從屬社區、國家或領土；一般而言，保護地在國防以及對外關係上會因而喪失控制權。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
